After upating JIRA server software to version @Enterprise Edition, Version: 3.13-#330@ Mylyn queries fail to synchronize.  Mylyn error message is as follows;

bq. 
Server error: unsupported content-encoding of '' found

Whilst I'm not an HTTP expert, I did commit the code to atlassian-gzipfilter that causes this bug.

The problem on the server-side is that it is not possible to null out a header once it has been set.  The closest you can get is to 'blank' it out - ie set it to an empty string.

You can see the code responsible to this here:
  http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRA-15658?focusedCommentId=131217#action_131217

From what I can tell of my reading of the HTTP spec - there are no problems with sending empty headers.  However, I'm happy to be proven wrong on this.

The particular code in Axis causing this problem is (from the only online source I could find in my 30 second look):
  http://tinyurl.com/3qtzb2

            Header contentEncoding = 
            	method.getResponseHeader(HTTPConstants.HEADER_CONTENT_ENCODING);
            if (contentEncoding != null) {
            	if (contentEncoding.getValue().
            			equalsIgnoreCase(HTTPConstants.COMPRESSION_GZIP)) {
            		releaseConnectionOnCloseStream = 
            			new GZIPInputStream(releaseConnectionOnCloseStream);
            	} else {
                    AxisFault fault = new AxisFault("HTTP",
                            "unsupported content-encoding of '" 
                    		+ contentEncoding.getValue()
                            + "' found", null, null);
                    throw fault;
            	}
            		
            }


So - really Axis should be doing a '!= ""' as well as a '!= null' on the contentEncoding value before throwing a hissy fit.

I'll do what I can do fix this in JIRA (see if there is a way to delay writing the header until the first byte has been written), but it seems that it should also be fixed in Axis.

This is a pity, because gzip encoding should make a large different to the transport speed of Mylyn & JIRA.  Sorry it hasn't worked in its first implementation.

